# Valkey Blog

Blog posts live in `content/blog/`. Each post is either a standalone `.md` file or a directory with an `index.md` (use a directory when you need to include images or other assets).

## Front matter

Every blog post must include TOML front matter between `+++` fences. Example:

```toml
+++
title = "Your Post Title"
date = 2026-04-01
description = "A short summary shown in the blog listing and metadata."
authors = ["github-username"]

[taxonomies]
blog_type = ["Announcements"]

[extra]
featured = false
featured_image = "/assets/media/featured/random-01.webp"
+++
```

### Required fields

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `title` | Post title |
| `date` | Publish date (`YYYY-MM-DD`) |
| `description` | Short summary for the blog listing |
| `authors` | List of GitHub usernames |
| `taxonomies.blog_type` | Post category (see below) |

### Optional fields

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `extra.featured` | Set to `true` to show in the Featured sidebar |
| `extra.featured_image` | Path to a featured image |

### Post types

The `blog_type` taxonomy is defined in `config.toml`. Current values:

- `Technical Deep Dive` — In-depth technical content
- `Announcements` — Releases, new features, project news
- `Community Highlight` — Community stories, year-in-review, ecosystem
- `How-to` — Tutorials and guides
- `Events` — Event recaps and announcements

To add a new type, add a post using it and update `sass/_valkey.scss` (badge color) and this README.

## Review process

PRs that add a new blog post with `blog_type` of **Technical Deep Dive** or **Announcements** will automatically have the `@valkey-io/technical-blog-reviewers` team requested as reviewers. Other post types are reviewed by the CODEOWNERS.

All commits must be signed off per the [DCO](https://developercertificate.org/) using `git commit --signoff`.

## File naming

Use the format `YYYY-MM-DD-slug.md` (or `YYYY-MM-DD-slug/index.md` for posts with assets).
